  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening capacity of employers&apos; organizations</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will strengthen the institutional capacity of employers&apos; organizations (EOs) to contribute to job rich growth through effective policy and social dialogue. This initiative is in line with ILO&#x2019;s response to the Syrian Crisis in Lebanon and with ILO&#x2019;s first Decent Work Country Programme for Lebanon. It will build upon the main achievements of ILO&#x2019;s work with EOs over the last few years and place employment issues on the national agenda. This project aims at developing solutions, in conformity with current Lebanese laws, by providing a solid foundation for sustained economic growth. Interventions will support business expansion and new investments in labour-intensive sectors, such as the agriculture and agro-food sector, while at the same time directly provide additional job opportunities for both Lebanese and Syrians. The focus will be to improve EO information on the agro-food sector; improve value chain development in agro-food; and improve provision of targeted services to member companies, mainly Business-to-Business Matchmaking services.</narrative>
  </description>
